This paper deals with learning causal Bayesian networks from a mixture of observational and experimental data. This topic is closely related to machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI), as well as statistical inference (cs.SI) and data science (cs.DS). Additionally, the paper involves the use of Bayesian methods (cs.IT) for learning the causal structure and parameters of the underlying causal process. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SI, cs.DS, and cs.IT.
